chunk_text:
sahadevah--Sahadeva; ca--and; sughosa-manipuspakau--the conches named
Sughosa and Manipuspaka; kasyah--the King of Kasi (Varanasi); ca--and;
parama-isu-asah--the great archer; sikhandi--Sikhandi; ca--also; maha-
rathah--one who can fight alone against thousands; dhrstadyumnah--
Dhrstadyumna (the son of King Drupada); viratah--Virata (the prince who
gave shelter to the Pandavas while they were in disguise); ca--also;
satyakih--Satyaki (the same as Yuyudhana, the charioteer of Lord
Krsna); ca--and; aparajitah--who were never vanquished before;
drupadah--Drupada, the King of Pancala; draupadeyah--the sons of
Draupadi; ca--also; sarvasah--all; prthivi-pate--O King; saubhadrah--
the son of Subhadra (Abhimanyu); ca--also; maha-bahuh--mighty-armed;
